Apart from checking the logs you can additionally ensure that the broker has enough headroom to operate in terms of CPU, RAM, Network, Disk, etc. It can be done using container monitoring solution like [docker stats][3] or [JMeter PerfMon Plugin][4]. If this is the case you might need to increase [container limits][5] or [Docker engine][6]  


